# Setting up the development enviroment
To use __Megazord Framework__ you must install the following tools:
1. [nodejs](https://nodejs.org/en/download/releases/) versiÃ³n 0.12

 > If you need permisions to install software use __sudo__ command.
 > Notice that you will need credentials to use it.

2. To verify the __node__ version run:
        node -v

3. npm
        npm install --global npm@latest

4. To verify the __npm__ version run:
        npm -v

 > If you need more than one version of node installed on your enviroment you can use __nvm__.
 > Allways be sure about what __node__ version you are working on.

5. Install __yeoman__
        npm install --global yo bower grunt-cli

6. Install __Megazord App Generator__
        npm install git+ssh://git@github.com:SYNERGY-GB/generator-megazord.git

7. Create a directory for your __Megazord App__
        mkdir <megazordAppName>
        cd <megazordAppName>

8. Create the app scafolding using __Megazord App Generator__
        yo megazord

9. Follow the steps and answer the questions from the __Megazord App Generator__
   

